text.section:
The board shall conduct examinations at least twice a year at such times and places as the board deems convenient for applicants for licenses to practice podiatry in this state, and shall admit to examination any applicant who:
Is at least eighteen (18) years of age;
Is a citizen of the United States and a resident of the State of Kentucky;
Is of good moral character and temperate habits; and
Has completed a course in and graduated from a school or college of podiatry approved by the board.
